snippet.textDisplay:
Its surreal!! the only Mohobbat Element I missed was Mohobbat with Almighty!! Ishq - e - Khuda, ALLAH se mohobbat to sab se topest hai, and 2AM is perfect "Tahajjud" time, if they would had created a room where a man or women talking to his Almighty, boy the goosebumps there would had been on another level.

Rest its a Masterpiece after Mehram, GO, this made me cry, i can relate to this song, I read somewhere on another video where somebody expressed his thoughts as It is a conversation between a Pessimist and optimist, Pessimist complains the negativity and optimist tells him that Love exists too! if you listen to this song with this perspective the impact goes 100x, and if you observe Star Shah's part showed people all alone and frustrated, while Zeeshans's part is all with couples!! and how can I forget the lyrics every word hits you.

This song will be in my head for sometime now and that sometime is not ending soon!!

snippet.textDisplay:
8:31 Nostalgia ! .... Had such a intimately beautiful moment just watching a "set", Instead of dead-green screens with track-marks!
Majority of the video could've been knocked out with meticulously planned match-motions & set extensions in post.... Agreed !....BUT....  
NO post-production "knowhow", could ever measure up to that almost visceral sensory overload of a physical set / even by a base unit!
That smell of volatile thinners, those foam board walls, the dusty props, smoke, nails & chaos ! .... Keep this art alive guys ! ♥
snippet.textOriginal:
